Prep time: 30' 
Easy 

Ingredients (4 persons): 
350-400gr of diced chicken 
350gr fresh vegetables (thai/wok mix) with onions (if not, add 1 onion) 
280gr pad thai 
3 eggs
3 tbsp sweet soy sauce
3 tbsp fish sauce (nuoc-mam) 
1 tbsp of roasted peanuts 
juice of 1/2 lime 
Paprika powder 
2 tbsp Peanut or sunflower oil 
2 garlic cloves, chopped or in pieces (if you want to remove them later) 
Salt & pepper

Sprinkle the diced chicken with the paprika powder and mix well. Leave to marinate in the fridge while you prepare the rest of your ingredients. 
Beat the eggs in a bowl and set aside. 
Prepare the rest of the ingredients and sauces. 
In a wok, put the peanut oil and let heat. Then add the garlic and sauté for 1 min. 
Add the chicken and heat for 4-5 minutes on medium heat. 
Prepare a saucepan and bring water to a boil for the pad thai. 
Add the vegetables in the wok, mix everything together and cook with the lid on for 5-10 minutes. 
Meanwhile, put the pad thai in the boiled water for 3-4 minutes. Then remove from the water and keep aside. 
Mix everything in the wok and make a small hole in the middle. Add the eggs and cook without mixing for 2 minutes until you have like an omelet. Then break the omelet and mix everything well. 
Add 2 tbsp of fish sauce and soy sauce and mix. 
Add the pad thai and mix gently so as not to break them. Add 1 tbsp of fish sauce and soy sauce. Pepper and a pinch of salt if you want (note: fish sauce is already salty). Add lime juice and half of the peanuts and mix everything. 
Serve and sprinkle each dish with the rest of the peanuts.

You can also replace the chicken with scampis. 
In this case, remove the scampis from the wok after step 5 and keep aside until step 9. 
Then add them again to prevent them from being overcooked. 

Enjoy! 

